:: Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Tentacles
<<set $location to "drain">><<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<gwylanHypnoCanvas>>
You find yourself in the storm drains beneath town. Water drips into the still canal beside you, each drop reflecting purple light.
<br><br>

A deep thump echoes through the tunnel, dislodging loose bricks from the ceiling. The caps of the pipes lining the waterway burst open, revealing grasping masses of purple tentacles. More than that, a shadow appears on the wall ahead, cast by something unseen. You hear the groan of tortured stone, like a great bulk forcing its way through, towards you.
<br><br>

From behind, a song echoes, loud enough to be heard beneath the groaning. It promises security, but this only agitates your anxiety. You turn and run towards the voice. Light continues to enter from the drains above, yet the tunnels around you darken, as if the dark itself were resisting, and growing stronger.
<br><br>

You come to a round room, with a pathway looping around a pool. In its centre a waterfall cascades, flowing into the water below without disturbing it. Within, a pair of eyes open, bearing a mischievous glimmer. It's Gwylan. <<He>> looks uncanny, as neither <<his>> hair nor clothes appear wet. <<He>> gives you a reassuring smile, then <<he>> reaches towards you. <<His>> hand presses against the side of the waterfall as if it were glass.
<br><br>

<<link [[Reach for Gwylan|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Tentacles 2]]>><<set $phase2 to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Step away|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Tentacles 2]]>><<set $phase2 to 2>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Tentacles 2
<<effects>>

<<if $phase2 is 1>>
	You reach for Gwylan, pushing your fingers into the waterfall. It feels like normal water, if warmer than you'd expect. Gwylan grasps your hand, then pulls you with an irresistible force.
<<else>>
	You turn away from the waterfall. The water becomes more violent, and you hear the voice again. It's the same song, but more firm this time, carrying the tone of an anxious parent telling their child to step away from danger.
	<br><br>

	The force of it proves irresistible. You step back to the waterfall, and reach in. It feels like normal water, if a bit cooler than usual.
<</if>>
<br><br>

A flash of green light fills your vision as you pass into the water, disorienting you. Your hands and knees find solid stone. Gwylan stands next to you, and crouches to help you to your feet. <<He>> looks oddly dry.
<br><br>

"You're not actually wet, you know," Gwylan says as if reading your mind. You look at the waterfall, <span class="pink">and see another pair of eyes staring back.</span>
<br><br>

"Don't look at it." Gwylan takes both your hands. "Look at me. Remember this waterfall, and where I brought you. Now your inability to forget works in your favour, see?"
<br><br>

<<link [[Ask for more details on what's going on|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Ask]]>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Nod|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Nod]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Plants
<<set $location to "farm_manors">><<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<gwylanHypnoCanvas>>
You find yourself within a circular clearing in a hedge maze, perhaps its centre. A statue looms above you, staring at the horizon. Vines grow up its entire body, wrapping around its limbs and neck. It looks tall enough to see over the hedge.
<br><br>

The statue creaks as the vines tighten around it with impossible strength. Then the head snaps off, the neck reduced to a rain of splinters. Freed from the statue, the vines whip towards you, groping the air inches from your skin.
<br><br>

You hear singing, blown to you on the wind. It promises security, but that only agitates your anxiety. You step away from the vines, and enter the maze, following the sound of the voice. The hedge around you sways in an unseen wind, but lacks the malice of the vines. For now.
<br><br>

You come to another clearing, this one dominated by a fountain. Water flies a dozen or more feet into the air, landing in a second tier before cascading to the main vessel. A pair of eyes, bearing a mischievous glimmer, stare up at you. It's Gwylan, lying on <<his>> back. <<He>> gives you a reassuring smile, then <<he>> lifts a hand and presses it against the surface, as if it were glass.
<br><br>

<<link [[Reach for Gwylan|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Plants 2]]>><<set $phase2 to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Step away|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Plants 2]]>><<set $phase2 to 2>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Plants 2
<<effects>>
<<if $phase2 is 1>>
	You reach into the water, and grasp Gwylan's fingers. With an irresistible force, <<he>> pulls you into the fountain.
<<else>>
	You turn away from the water, but Gwylan's song calls to you again, taking on a firmer tone, like an anxious parent calling their child away from danger. It proves an irresistible force. You turn back to the fountain. Gwylan takes your hand, and pulls you in.
<</if>>
<br><br>

It's deeper than it looked, and your surroundings disappear in a disorienting flash of green light. Then you're on your hands and knees in shallow water, the fountain's water cascading on your back. Gwylan crouches, and helps you from the fountain. <<Hes>> somehow dry.
<br><br>

"You're not actually wet either, you know," Gwylan says, as if <<he>> read your mind. You look at the water, <span class="pink">and see a pair of eyes staring back.</span>
<br><br>

"Don't look at it." Gwylan takes both your hands. "Look at me. Remember this fountain, and where I brought you. Now your inability to forget works in your favour, see?"
<br><br>

<<link [[Ask for more details on what's going on|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Ask]]>><</link>>
