:: Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Monsters
<<set $location to "forest">><<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<gwylanHypnoCanvas>>
You find yourself elsewhere in the forest. Branches fork and twist above you, groping the sky. You put your hands on wiry grass, and push yourself into a sitting position.
<br><br>

A bullet blasts apart a nearby tree. You jump to your feet and, spinning in the direction of the shot, find a pair of wolf people.
<br><br>

"Blast!"
<br>
"I told you you'd miss. Give me the gun."
<br>
"One more try. Look, its stunned in fright."
<br><br>

You hear singing behind you. It promises security, yet that only agitates your anxiety. Lacking options, you turn and run in the direction of the voice.
<br><br>

You come to a still lake, but it's not the lake you're familiar with. It looks deep, even here at the shore. A sheer drop, if not for the water, with no bottom visible.
<br><br>

A pair of eyes appear beneath you, a mischievous glimmer clear despite the distortion of the water. It's Gwylan. <<He>> gives you a reassuring smile, then reaches towards you, stopping just short of the surface. <<His>> fingertips press against it, as if it were glass.
<br><br>

<<link [[Reach for Gwylan|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Monsters 2]]>><<set $phase2 to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Step away|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Monsters 2]]>><<set $phase2 to 2>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Monsters 2
<<effects>>

<<if $phase2 is 1>>
	You crouch, and reach in. It feels like normal, cool lake water.
<<else>>
	You step away from the lake. The surface stirs, and you hear the voice again. It's the same song, but more firm this time, carrying the tone of an anxious parent telling their child to step away from danger.
	<br><br>

	The force of it proves irresistible. You step back to the lake, and reach in. It feels like normal, cool lake water.
<</if>>
<br><br>

Gwylan takes your hand in <<hers>>, flashes an apologetic smile, then pulls you towards <<him>> with an irresistible strength. You plunge into the water, and for a disorienting moment your surroundings vanish in a flash of green light.
<br><br>

Your hands and knees find solid ground, and you push yourself to your feet, emerging from the water. It's shallower than it appeared. Gwylan grasps your shoulder, and helps keep your slick feet steady. <<He>> looks dry, somehow.
<br><br>

"You're not actually wet either, you know," Gwylan says as if reading your mind. You look back at the water. It appears deep again, <span class="pink">and another pair of eyes stare back.</span>
<br><br>

"Don't look at it." Gwylan takes both your hands. "Look at me. Remember this lake, and where I brought you. Now your inability to forget works in your favour, see?"
<br><br>

<<link [[Ask for more details on what's going on|Gwylan Hypnosis Insight Ask]]>><</link>>
